gence of AI-driven digital twins is revolutionizing urban planning and smart city operations, offering enhanced predictive capabilities for cities. Evidence from the sources highlights various applications of these technologies, such as improving planning accuracy and operational efficiency in European smart cities and integrating privacy-enhancing technologies to safeguard data. This transformation is crucial for the building-envelope industry, as it enables more sustainable and responsive architectural designs that can adapt to evolving urban environments.", "rationale": "The trend is primarily driven by technological advancements in AI and digital twin capabilities which enhance urban planning and efficiency. This is evidenced by the emerging applications in smart cities and the importance of predictive capabilities for architectural designs noted in various sources."}}	\N
