55	55	10	Integration of Smart Technologies in Building Design	The building envelope industry is witnessing a significant shift towards integrating smart technologies, including building integrated photovoltaics (BIPV) and IoT applications, to enhance energy efficiency and sustainability. Sources highlight advancements in technologies like BIPV systems for roofs and facades, as well as the deployment of IoT for smart home automation, indicating a convergence of environmental goals and technological innovation. This integration is crucial for achieving net-zero emissions and decarbonizing urban settings, positioning companies like Schüco to lead in sustainable building solutions.	megatrend	0	[{"url": "https://openalex.org/W4388723541", "title": "Increasing Solar Reflectivity of Building Envelope Materials to Mitigate Urban Heat Islands: State-of-the-Art Review"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W4306399840", "title": "Comparative review of international approaches to net-zero buildings: Knowledge-sharing initiative to develop design strategies for greenhouse gas emissions reduction"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W4224213039", "title": "Strategies to achieve a carbon neutral society: a review"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W4210786314", "title": "Facades-as-a-Service: The Role of Technology in the Circular Servitisation of the Building Envelope"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W4285277461", "title": "Perspective on the hydrogen economy as a pathway to reach net-zero CO <sub>2</sub> emissions in Europe"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W3178870234", "title": "Investigating Smart City Development Based on Green Buildings, Electrical Vehicles and Feasible Indicators"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W3083961595", "title": "Review of technological design options for building integrated photovoltaics (BIPV)"}, {"url": "https://openalex.org/W3021124964", "title": "A Systematic Content Review of Artificial Intelligence and the Internet of Things Applications in Smart Home"}]
